label.value: Biomedical Concept Property

value.value: A characteristic from a set of characteristics used to define a biomedical concept.

label.value: Biomedical Concept Property Name

value.value: The literal identifier (i.e., distinctive designation) of the biomedical concept property.

label.value: Biomedical Concept Property Required Indicator

value.value: An indication as to whether the biomedical concept property is required.

label.value: Biomedical Concept Property Enabled Indicator

value.value: An indication as to whether the biomedical concept property is activated for use within a given usage context for a biomedical concept.

label.value: Non-Clear Cell Renal Cell Carcinoma

value.value: A group of renal cell carcinomas characterized by the absence of lipid-containing clear adenocarcinoma cells. This category includes the following morphological subtypes: papillary renal cell carcinoma; sarcomatoid renal cell carcinoma; chromophobe renal cell carcinoma; tubulocystic renal cell carcinoma; and eosinophilic solid and cystic renal cell carcinoma.

label.value: PROMIS Pediatric and Parent Proxy Social Health Domain

value.value: The set of PROMIS measures that assess the social health of pediatric subjects through self-report or parent proxy report.

label.value: PROMIS Relationships/Social Support Subordinate Domain

value.value: The collection of PROMIS item scales that assess an individual's relationships and social support.

label.value: Tyrphostin A8

value.value: A member of the tyrphostin family of tyrosine kinase inhibitors that inhibits the GTPase activity of transducin and competitively inhibits calcineurin activity. (NCI)

label.value: ES02

value.value: Provider: ES Cell International Pte Ltd., Melbourne, Australia. Information from provider and not independently verified by NIH: Cells are positive for cell markers Oct-4, SSEA-4, TRA-1-60, GCTM-2, and alkaline phosphatase activity; Cells are negative for cell marker SSEA-1; Give rise to teratomas containing derivatives of three germ layers in SCID mice; Differentiate in vitro into extraembryonic and somatic cell lineages; Neural progenitor cells may be isolated from differentiating ES cell cultures and induced to form mature neurons; Available for distribution. This cell line meets the criteria for the use of human embryonic stem cells by federally funded researchers.

label.value: Locally Advanced Unresectable Digestive System Adenocarcinoma

value.value: Digestive system adenocarcinoma that has spread from its original site of growth to nearby tissues or lymph nodes and is not amenable to surgical resection.
